uk.ac.manchester.cs.hobo.model

Class DModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.hobo.model.DModel

  • public class DModel
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the HOBO direct model, which is an Object Model (OM) within which domain concepts are represented directly by domain-specific Java classes (OM classes). The direct model will be associated with a Frames Model (FM), as represented via a CModel object.

    Each class in the OM will implement the DObject interface and will be bound to a CFrame object in the FM. The OM fields associated with the OM classes will be represented via DField objects of the different types and will be bound to a CSlot objects in the FM.
